quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  97,1,"We sent it{1}down on the Night of Determination.",footnotes:1:The Qur’an.
  97,2,"But what can make you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>realize what the Night of Determination is?"
  97,3,"The Night of Determination is better than a thousand months—"
  97,4,"in it descend the angels, with the Spirit{1}among them, by the leave of their Lord with every command.",footnotes:1:Angel Gabriel (Jibreel).
  97,5,"Peace! It is until the <span class=""h"">rise<sup foot_note=""81488"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>of dawn."
  98,1,"Those who have denied from among the People of the Scripture and the polytheists were not to be parted<i class=""s"">(from disbelief) </i>until the evident proof came to them—"
  98,2,"a messenger from Allah reading purified Scrolls;"
  98,3,"in them are valuable scriptures."
  98,4,"Nor did those who were given the Scripture become divided except after the evident proof came to them."
  98,5,"And they were only commanded to worship Allah—devoting religion to Him, turning away from all that is false—and to establish the prayer and to bring{1}the purifying charity{2}, and that is the religion{3}most upright.",footnotes:1:The Qur’an always uses verb ‘to bring’ rather than verb ‘to give’ in association with charity; this should be pondered by the reader.|2:The Arabic word used is zakāt, which denotes purification and growth.|3:The Arabic word used is deenwhich means ‘a way of life’, ‘religion’ or ‘recompense’.
  98,6,"Indeed, those who have denied among the People of the Scripture and the polytheists are in the fire of Hell, abiding therein; those are the worst of all beings."
  98,7,"Indeed, those who have attained faith and have done righteous deeds—those are the best of all beings."
